  <Name>k__BackingField: Job
  fancyName: 
  nickname: job
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Character and Wealth"
      title: "Job\u2019s Character and Wealth"
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a man in the land of Uz whose name was Job, and that
        man was blameless and upright, one who feared God and turned away from evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There were born to him seven sons and three daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He possessed 7,000 sheep, 3,000 camels, 500 yoke of oxen, and 500
        female donkeys, and very many servants, so that this man was the greatest
        of all the people of the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'His sons used to go and hold a feast in the house of each one on
        his day, and they would send and invite their three sisters to eat and drink
        with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Satan Allowed to Test Job'
      title: Satan Allowed to Test Job
      number: 5
      content: "And when the days of the feast had run their course, Job would send
        and consecrate them, and he would rise early in the morning and offer burnt
        offerings according to the number of them all. For Job said, \u201CIt may
        be that my children have sinned, and cursed[[COMMENT(0)]] God in their hearts.\u201D
        Thus Job did continually.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: The Hebrew word is used euphemistically for in 1:5, 11; 2:5, 9
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now there was a day when the sons of God came to present themselves
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and Satan[[COMMENT(0)]] also came
        among them. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: "Hebrew or ; so throughout chapters 1\u20132"
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Satan, \u201CFrom where have
        you come?\u201D Satan answered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said,
        \u201CFrom going to and fro on the earth, and from walking up and down on
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Satan, \u201CHave you
        considered my servant Job, that there is none like him on the earth, a blameless
        and upright man, who fears God and turns away from evil?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Satan answered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said, \u201CDoes
        Job fear God for no reason? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Have you not put a hedge around him and his house and all that he
        has, on every side? You have blessed the work of his hands, and his possessions
        have increased in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But stretch out your hand and touch all that he has, and he will
        curse you to your face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Satan Takes Job\u2019s Property and Children"
      title: "Satan Takes Job\u2019s Property and Children"
      number: 12
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Satan, \u201CBehold,
        all that he has is in your hand. Only against him do not stretch out your
        hand.\u201D So Satan went out from the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now there was a day when his sons and daughters were eating and drinking
        wine in their oldest brother\u2019s house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and there came a messenger to Job and said, \u201CThe oxen were plowing
        and the donkeys feeding beside them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and the Sabeans fell upon them and took them and struck down the
        servants[[COMMENT(0)]] with the edge of the sword, and I alone have escaped
        to tell you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '1:15 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verses 16, 17
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "While he was yet speaking, there came another and said, \u201CThe
        fire of God fell from heaven and burned up the sheep and the servants and
        consumed them, and I alone have escaped to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "While he was yet speaking, there came another and said, \u201CThe
        Chaldeans formed three groups and made a raid on the camels and took them
        and struck down the servants with the edge of the sword, and I alone have
        escaped to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "While he was yet speaking, there came another and said, \u201CYour
        sons and daughters were eating and drinking wine in their oldest brother\u2019s
        house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and behold, a great wind came across the wilderness and struck the
        four corners of the house, and it fell upon the young people, and they are
        dead, and I alone have escaped to tell you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Job arose and tore his robe and shaved his head and fell on
        the ground and worshiped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he said, \u201CNaked I came from my mother\u2019s womb, and naked
        shall I return. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  gave, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has taken away; blessed be the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  In all this Job did not sin or charge God with wrong.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Satan Attacks Job\u2019s Health"
      title: "Satan Attacks Job\u2019s Health"
      number: 1
      content: '  Again there was a day when the sons of God came to present themselves
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and Satan also came among them to
        present himself before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Satan, \u201CFrom where
        have you come?\u201D Satan answered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said,
        \u201CFrom going to and fro on the earth, and from walking up and down on
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Satan, \u201CHave you
        considered my servant Job, that there is none like him on the earth, a blameless
        and upright man, who fears God and turns away from evil? He still holds fast
        his integrity, although you incited me against him to destroy him without
        reason.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Satan answered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said, \u201CSkin
        for skin! All that a man has he will give for his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But stretch out your hand and touch his bone and his flesh, and he
        will curse you to your face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Satan, \u201CBehold,
        he is in your hand; only spare his life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Satan went out from the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and struck Job with loathsome sores from the sole of his foot to the crown
        of his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he took a piece of broken pottery with which to scrape himself
        while he sat in the ashes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then his wife said to him, \u201CDo you still hold fast your integrity?
        Curse God and die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Job\u2019s Three Friends"
      title: "Job\u2019s Three Friends"
      number: 10
      content: "But he said to her, \u201CYou speak as one of the foolish women would
        speak. Shall we receive good from God, and shall we not receive evil?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        In all this Job did not sin with his lips.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:10 '
        content: Or ; also verse 11
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now when Job\u2019s three friends heard of all this evil that had
        come upon him, they came each from his own place, Eliphaz the Temanite, Bildad
        the Shuhite, and Zophar the Naamathite. They made an appointment together
        to come to show him sympathy and comfort him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when they saw him from a distance, they did not recognize him.
        And they raised their voices and wept, and they tore their robes and sprinkled
        dust on their heads toward heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And they sat with him on the ground seven days and seven nights, and
        no one spoke a word to him, for they saw that his suffering was very great.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Laments His Birth'
      title: Job Laments His Birth
      number: 1
      content: '  After this Job opened his mouth and cursed the day of his birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Job said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u201CLet the day perish on which I was born,and the night that
        said,\u2018A man is conceived.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let that day be darkness!May God above not seek it,nor light shine
        upon it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let gloom and deep darkness claim it.Let clouds dwell upon it;let
        the blackness of the day terrify it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "That night\u2014let thick darkness seize it!Let it not rejoice among
        the days of the year;let it not come into the number of the months.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Behold, let that night be barren;let no joyful cry enter it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let those curse it who curse the day,who are ready to rouse up Leviathan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let the stars of its dawn be dark;let it hope for light, but have
        none,nor see the eyelids of the morning,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "because it did not shut the doors of my mother\u2019s womb,nor hide
        trouble from my eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWhy did I not die at birth,come out from the womb and expire?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Why did the knees receive me?Or why the breasts, that I should nurse?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For then I would have lain down and been quiet;I would have slept;
        then I would have been at rest,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'with kings and counselors of the earthwho rebuilt ruins for themselves,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'or with princes who had gold,who filled their houses with silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Or why was I not as a hidden stillborn child,as infants who never
        see the light?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'There the wicked cease from troubling,and there the weary are at
        rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There the prisoners are at ease together;they hear not the voice
        of the taskmaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The small and the great are there,and the slave is free from his
        master.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhy is light given to him who is in misery,and life to the
        bitter in soul,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'who long for death, but it comes not,and dig for it more than for
        hidden treasures,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'who rejoice exceedinglyand are glad when they find the grave?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Why is light given to a man whose way is hidden,whom God has hedged
        in?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For my sighing comes instead of[[COMMENT(0)]] my bread,and my groanings
        are poured out like water.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:24 '
        content: 'Or ; Hebrew '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  For the thing that I fear comes upon me,and what I dread befalls
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I am not at ease, nor am I quiet;I have no rest, but trouble comes.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz Speaks: The Innocent Prosper'
      title: 'Eliphaz Speaks: The Innocent Prosper'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf one ventures a word with you, will you be impatient?Yet
        who can keep from speaking?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Behold, you have instructed many,and you have strengthened the weak
        hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Your words have upheld him who was stumbling,and you have made firm
        the feeble knees.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But now it has come to you, and you are impatient;it touches you,
        and you are dismayed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Is not your fear of God[[COMMENT(0)]] your confidence,and the integrity
        of your ways your hope?  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CRemember: who that was innocent ever perished?Or where were
        the upright cut off?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'As I have seen, those who plow iniquityand sow trouble reap the same.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'By the breath of God they perish,and by the blast of his anger they
        are consumed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The roar of the lion, the voice of the fierce lion,  the teeth of
        the young lions are broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The strong lion perishes for lack of prey,and the cubs of the lioness
        are scattered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CNow a word was brought to me stealthily;my ear received the
        whisper of it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Amid thoughts from visions of the night,when deep sleep falls on
        men,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'dread came upon me, and trembling,which made all my bones shake.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'A spirit glided past my face;the hair of my flesh stood up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It stood still,but I could not discern its appearance.  A form was
        before my eyes;there was silence, then I heard a voice:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u2018Can mortal man be in the right before[[COMMENT(0)]] God?Can
        a man be pure before his Maker?  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:17 '
        content: Or ; twice in this verse
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Even in his servants he puts no trust,and his angels he charges with
        error;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'how much more those who dwell in houses of clay,whose foundation
        is in the dust,who are crushed like[[COMMENT(0)]]  the moth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Between morning and evening they are beaten to pieces;they perish
        forever without anyone regarding it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Is not their tent-cord plucked up within them,  do they not die,
        and that without wisdom?\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CCall now; is there anyone who will answer you?To which of
        the holy ones will you turn?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Surely vexation kills the fool,and jealousy slays the simple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  I have seen the fool taking root,but suddenly I cursed his dwelling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'His children are far from safety;they are crushed in the gate,and
        there is no one to deliver them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The hungry eat his harvest,and he takes it even out of thorns,[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        the thirsty pant after his wealth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: 'The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertainAquila, Symmachus, Syriac,
          Vulgate; Hebrew could be read as Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For affliction does not come from the dust,nor does trouble sprout
        from the ground,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but man is born to troubleas the sparks fly upward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAs for me, I would seek God,and to God would I commit my cause,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'who does great things and unsearchable,  marvelous things without
        number:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'he gives rain on the earthand sends waters on the fields;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'he sets on high those who are lowly,and those who mourn are lifted
        to safety.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He frustrates the devices of the crafty,so that their hands achieve
        no success.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He catches the wise in their own craftiness,and the schemes of the
        wily are brought to a quick end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They meet with darkness in the daytimeand grope at noonday as in
        the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But he saves the needy from the sword of their mouthand from the
        hand of the mighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the poor have hope,and injustice shuts her mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBehold, blessed is the one whom God reproves;therefore despise
        not the discipline of the Almighty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For he wounds, but he binds up;he shatters, but his hands heal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He will deliver you from six troubles;in seven no evil[[COMMENT(0)]]
        shall touch you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  In famine he will redeem you from death,and in war from the power
        of the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You shall be hidden from the lash of the tongue,and shall not fear
        destruction when it comes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'At destruction and famine you shall laugh,and shall not fear the
        beasts of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For you shall be in league with the stones of the field,and the beasts
        of the field shall be at peace with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall know that your tent is at peace,and you shall inspect your
        fold and miss nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall know also that your offspring shall be many,and your descendants
        as the grass of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You shall come to your grave in ripe old age,like a sheaf gathered
        up in its season.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Behold, this we have searched out; it is true.Hear, and know it for
        your good.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: '5:27 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Replies: My Complaint Is Just'
      title: 'Job Replies: My Complaint Is Just'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COh that my vexation were weighed,and all my calamity laid in
        the balances!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For then it would be heavier than the sand of the sea;therefore my
        words have been rash.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the arrows of the Almighty are in me;my spirit drinks their poison;the
        terrors of God are arrayed against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Does the wild donkey bray when he has grass,or the ox low over his
        fodder?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Can that which is tasteless be eaten without salt,or is there any
        taste in the juice of the mallow?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'My appetite refuses to touch them;they are as food that is loathsome
        to me.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:7 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201COh that I might have my request,and that God would fulfill
        my hope,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'that it would please God to crush me,that he would let loose his
        hand and cut me off!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This would be my comfort;I would even exult[[COMMENT(0)]] in pain
        unsparing,for I have not denied the words of the Holy One.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:10 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'What is my strength, that I should wait?And what is my end, that
        I should be patient?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Is my strength the strength of stones, or is my flesh bronze?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Have I any help in me,when resource is driven from me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CHe who withholds[[COMMENT(0)]] kindness from a friendforsakes
        the fear of the Almighty.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:14 '
        content: Syriac, Vulgate (compare Targum); the meaning of the Hebrew word
          is uncertain
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My brothers are treacherous as a torrent-bed,as torrential streams
        that pass away,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'which are dark with ice,and where the snow hides itself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When they melt, they disappear;when it is hot, they vanish from their
        place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The caravans turn aside from their course;they go up into the waste
        and perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The caravans of Tema look,the travelers of Sheba hope.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They are ashamed because they were confident;they come there and
        are disappointed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For you have now become nothing;you see my calamity and are afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Have I said, \u2018Make me a gift\u2019?Or, \u2018From your wealth
        offer a bribe for me\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Or, \u2018Deliver me from the adversary\u2019s hand\u2019?Or, \u2018Redeem
        me from the hand of the ruthless\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CTeach me, and I will be silent;make me understand how I have
        gone astray.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'How forceful are upright words!But what does reproof from you reprove?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Do you think that you can reprove words,when the speech of a despairing
        man is wind?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You would even cast lots over the fatherless,and bargain over your
        friend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CBut now, be pleased to look at me,for I will not lie to your
        face.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Please turn; let no injustice be done.Turn now; my vindication
        is at stake.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Is there any injustice on my tongue?Cannot my palate discern the cause
        of calamity?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues: My Life Has No Hope'
      title: 'Job Continues: My Life Has No Hope'
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CHas not man a hard service on earth,and are not his days
        like the days of a hired hand?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Like a slave who longs for the shadow,and like a hired hand who looks
        for his wages,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'so I am allotted months of emptiness,  and nights of misery are apportioned
        to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  When I lie down I say, \u2018When shall I arise?\u2019But the night
        is long,and I am full of tossing till the dawn.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My flesh is clothed with worms and dirt;my skin hardens, then breaks
        out afresh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "My days are swifter than a weaver\u2019s shuttleand come to their
        end without hope.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CRemember that my life is a breath;my eye will never again see
        good.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The eye of him who sees me will behold me no more;while your eyes
        are on me, I shall be gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'As the cloud fades and vanishes,so he who goes down to Sheol does
        not come up;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'he returns no more to his house,nor does his place know him anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTherefore I will not restrain my mouth;I will speak in the
        anguish of my spirit;I will complain in the bitterness of my soul.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Am I the sea, or a sea monster,that you set a guard over me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  When I say, \u2018My bed will comfort me,my couch will ease my
        complaint,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then you scare me with dreamsand terrify me with visions,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so that I would choose stranglingand death rather than my bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I loathe my life; I would not live forever.  Leave me alone, for
        my days are a breath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  What is man, that you make so much of him,and that you set your
        heart on him,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  visit him every morningand test him every moment?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'How long will you not look away from me,nor leave me alone till I
        swallow my spit?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'If I sin, what do I do to you, you watcher of mankind?Why have you
        made me your mark?Why have I become a burden to you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Why do you not pardon my transgressionand take away my iniquity?For
        now I shall lie in the earth;you will seek me, but I shall not be.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad Speaks: Job Should Repent'
      title: 'Bildad Speaks: Job Should Repent'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you say these things,and the words of your mouth
        be a great wind?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Does God pervert justice?Or does the Almighty pervert the right?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If your children have sinned against him,he has delivered them into
        the hand of their transgression.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If you will seek Godand plead with the Almighty for mercy,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'if you are pure and upright,surely then he will rouse himself for
        youand restore your rightful habitation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And though your beginning was small,  your latter days will be very
        great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CFor inquire, please, of bygone ages,and consider what the fathers
        have searched out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For we are but of yesterday and know nothing,for our days on earth
        are a shadow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Will they not teach you and tell youand utter words out of their
        understanding?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CCan papyrus grow where there is no marsh?Can reeds flourish
        where there is no water?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'While yet in flower and not cut down,they wither before any other
        plant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Such are the paths of all who forget God;  the hope of the godless
        shall perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "His confidence is severed,and his trust is a spider\u2019s web.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He leans against his house, but it does not stand;he lays hold of
        it, but it does not endure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He is a lush plant before the sun,and his shoots spread over his
        garden.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'His roots entwine the stone heap;he looks upon a house of stones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If he is destroyed from his place,then it will deny him, saying,
        \u2018I have never seen you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, this is the joy of his way,and out of the soil others will
        spring.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBehold, God will not reject a blameless man,nor take the hand
        of evildoers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He will yet fill your mouth with laughter,and your lips with shouting.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Those who hate you will be clothed with shame,and the tent of the
        wicked will be no more.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Replies: There Is No Arbiter'
      title: 'Job Replies: There Is No Arbiter'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTruly I know that it is so:But how can a man be in the right
        before God?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If one wished to contend with him,one could not answer him once in
        a thousand times.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He is wise in heart and mighty in strength\u2014who has hardened
        himself against him, and succeeded?\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'he who removes mountains, and they know it not,when he overturns
        them in his anger,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'who shakes the earth out of its place,and its pillars tremble;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'who commands the sun, and it does not rise;who seals up the stars;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'who alone stretched out the heavensand trampled the waves of the
        sea;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'who made the Bear and Orion,the Pleiades and the chambers of the
        south;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'who does great things beyond searching out,and marvelous things beyond
        number.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, he passes by me, and I see him not;he moves on, but I do
        not perceive him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Behold, he snatches away; who can turn him back?  Who will say to
        him, \u2018What are you doing?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGod will not turn back his anger;beneath him bowed the helpers
        of Rahab.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  How then can I answer him,choosing my words with him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Though I am in the right, I cannot answer him;I must appeal for
        mercy to my accuser.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If I summoned him and he answered me,I would not believe that he
        was listening to my voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For he crushes me with a tempestand multiplies my wounds without
        cause;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'he will not let me get my breath,but fills me with bitterness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If it is a contest of strength, behold, he is mighty!If it is a matter
        of justice, who can summon him?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Though I am in the right, my own mouth would condemn me;though I
        am blameless, he would prove me perverse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I am blameless; I regard not myself;I loathe my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "It is all one; therefore I say,\u2018He destroys both the blameless
        and the wicked.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When disaster brings sudden death,he mocks at the calamity[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of the innocent.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:23 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  The earth is given into the hand of the wicked;he covers the faces
        of its judges\u2014  if it is not he, who then is it?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CMy days are swifter than a runner;they flee away; they see
        no good.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They go by like skiffs of reed,like an eagle swooping on the prey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If I say, \u2018I will forget my complaint,I will put off my sad
        face, and be of good cheer,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'I become afraid of all my suffering,for I know you will not hold
        me innocent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I shall be condemned;why then do I labor in vain?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'If I wash myself with snowand cleanse my hands with lye,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'yet you will plunge me into a pit,and my own clothes will abhor me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For he is not a man, as I am, that I might answer him,that we should
        come to trial together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  There is no[[COMMENT(0)]] arbiter between us,who might lay his
        hand on us both.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:33 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '  Let him take his rod away from me,and let not dread of him terrify
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Then I would speak without fear of him,for I am not so in myself.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues: A Plea to God'
      title: 'Job Continues: A Plea to God'
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CI loathe my life;I will give free utterance to my complaint;I
        will speak in the bitterness of my soul.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will say to God, Do not condemn me;let me know why you contend
        against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Does it seem good to you to oppress,to despise the work of your
        hands  and favor the designs of the wicked?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Have you eyes of flesh?  Do you see as man sees?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Are your days as the days of man,or your years as a man\u2019s years,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'that you seek out my iniquityand search for my sin,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'although you know that I am not guilty,and there is none to deliver
        out of your hand?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Your hands fashioned and made me,and now you have destroyed me
        altogether.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Remember that you have made me like clay;and will you return me to
        the dust?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Did you not pour me out like milkand curdle me like cheese?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You clothed me with skin and flesh,and knit me together with bones
        and sinews.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You have granted me life and steadfast love,and your care has preserved
        my spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet these things you hid in your heart;I know that this was your
        purpose.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If I sin, you watch meand do not acquit me of my iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  If I am guilty, woe to me!If I am in the right, I cannot lift up
        my head,for I am filled with disgraceand look on my affliction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And were my head lifted up,[[COMMENT(0)]] you would hunt me like
        a lionand again work wonders against me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You renew your witnesses against meand increase your vexation toward
        me;you bring fresh troops against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  \u201CWhy did you bring me out from the womb?Would that I had died
        before any eye had seen me  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  and were as though I had not been,carried from the womb to the
        grave.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Are not my days few?  Then cease, and leave me alone, that I may
        find a little cheer  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "before I go\u2014and I shall not return\u2014to the land of darkness
        and deep shadow,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "the land of gloom like thick darkness,like deep shadow without any
        order,where light is as thick darkness.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zophar Speaks: You Deserve Worse'
      title: 'Zophar Speaks: You Deserve Worse'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShould a multitude of words go unanswered,and a man full of
        talk be judged right?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Should your babble silence men,and when you mock, shall no one shame
        you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For you say, \u2018My doctrine is pure,and I am clean in God\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]]
        eyes.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But oh, that God would speakand open his lips to you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and that he would tell you the secrets of wisdom!For he is manifold
        in understanding.[[COMMENT(0)]]Know then that God exacts of you less than
        your guilt deserves.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:6 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CCan you find out the deep things of God?Can you find out
        the limit of the Almighty?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "It is higher than heaven[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014what can you do?Deeper
        than Sheol\u2014what can you know?  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Its measure is longer than the earthand broader than the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If he passes through and imprisonsand summons the court, who can
        turn him back?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For he knows worthless men;when he sees iniquity, will he not consider
        it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But a stupid man will get understandingwhen a wild donkey\u2019s
        colt is born a man!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf you prepare your heart,you will stretch out your hands toward
        him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If iniquity is in your hand, put it far away,and let not injustice
        dwell in your tents.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Surely then you will lift up your face without blemish;you will be
        secure and will not fear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You will forget your misery;you will remember it as waters that have
        passed away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And your life will be brighter than the noonday;its darkness will
        be like the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you will feel secure, because there is hope;you will look around
        and take your rest in security.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You will lie down, and none will make you afraid;many will court
        your favor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the eyes of the wicked will fail;all way of escape will be lost
        to them,and their hope is to breathe their last.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Replies: The  Has Done This'
      title: 'Job Replies: The  Has Done This'
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Then Job answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNo doubt you are the people,and wisdom will die with you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But I have understanding as well as you;I am not inferior to you.Who
        does not know such things as these?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I am a laughingstock to my friends;I, who called to God and he answered
        me,a just and blameless man, am a laughingstock.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In the thought of one who is at ease there is contempt for misfortune;it
        is ready for those whose feet slip.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The tents of robbers are at peace,and those who provoke God are
        secure,who bring their god in their hand.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:6 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut ask the beasts, and they will teach you;the birds of the
        heavens, and they will tell you;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'or the bushes of the earth, and they will teach you;[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        the fish of the sea will declare to you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who among all these does not knowthat the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has done this?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In his hand is the life of every living thingand the breath of all
        mankind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Does not the ear test wordsas the palate tastes food?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Wisdom is with the aged,and understanding in length of days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CWith God[[COMMENT(0)]] are wisdom and might;he has counsel
        and understanding.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If he tears down, none can rebuild;if he shuts a man in, none can
        open.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If he withholds the waters, they dry up;if he sends them out, they
        overwhelm the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'With him are strength and sound wisdom;the deceived and the deceiver
        are his.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He leads counselors away stripped,and judges he makes fools.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He looses the bonds of kingsand binds a waistcloth on their hips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He leads priests away strippedand overthrows the mighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He deprives of speech those who are trusted  and takes away the discernment
        of the elders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He pours contempt on princesand loosens the belt of the strong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He uncovers the deeps out of darknessand brings deep darkness to
        light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He makes nations great, and he destroys them;he enlarges nations,
        and leads them away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He takes away understanding from the chiefs of the people of the
        earthand makes them wander in a trackless waste.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: They grope in the dark without light,and he makes them stagger like
        a drunken man.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues: Still I Will Hope in God'
      title: 'Job Continues: Still I Will Hope in God'
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBehold, my eye has seen all this,my ear has heard and understood
        it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  What you know, I also know;I am not inferior to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  But I would speak to the Almighty,and I desire to argue my case
        with God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As for you, you whitewash with lies;  worthless physicians are you
        all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Oh that you would keep silent,and it would be your wisdom!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Hear now my argumentand listen to the pleadings of my lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Will you speak falsely for Godand speak deceitfully for him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Will you show partiality toward him?Will you plead the case for God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will it be well with you when he searches you out?Or can you deceive
        him, as one deceives a man?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He will surely rebuke youif in secret you show partiality.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Will not his majesty terrify you,and the dread of him fall upon you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Your maxims are proverbs of ashes;your defenses are defenses of clay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CLet me have silence, and I will speak,and let come on me what
        may.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Why should I take my flesh in my teethand put my life in my hand?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Though he slay me, I will hope in him;[[COMMENT(0)]]yet I will
        argue my ways to his face.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'This will be my salvation,that the godless shall not come before
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Keep listening to my words,and let my declaration be in your ears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Behold, I have prepared my case;I know that I shall be in the right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Who is there who will contend with me?For then I would be silent
        and die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Only grant me two things,then I will not hide myself from your face:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  withdraw your hand far from me,and let not dread of you terrify
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Then call, and I will answer;or let me speak, and you reply to
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'How many are my iniquities and my sins?  Make me know my transgression
        and my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Why do you hide your faceand count me as your enemy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Will you frighten a driven leafand pursue dry chaff?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For you write bitter things against meand make me inherit the iniquities
        of my youth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You put my feet in the stocksand watch all my paths;you set a limit
        for[[COMMENT(0)]] the soles of my feet.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:27 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Man[[COMMENT(0)]] wastes away like a rotten thing,like a garment that
        is moth-eaten.
      comments:
      - number: '13:28 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues: Death Comes Soon to All'
      title: 'Job Continues: Death Comes Soon to All'
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CMan who is born of a womanis few of days and full of trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He comes out like a flower and withers;he flees like a shadow and
        continues not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And do you open your eyes on such a oneand bring me into judgment
        with you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Who can bring a clean thing out of an unclean?There is not one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Since his days are determined,and the number of his months is with
        you,and you have appointed his limits that he cannot pass,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  look away from him and leave him alone,[[COMMENT(0)]]that he may
        enjoy, like a hired hand, his day.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:6 '
        content: 'Probable reading; Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFor there is hope for a tree,if it be cut down, that it will
        sprout again,and that its shoots will not cease.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Though its root grow old in the earth,and its stump die in the soil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'yet at the scent of water it will budand put out branches like a
        young plant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But a man dies and is laid low;man breathes his last, and where is
        he?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  As waters fail from a lakeand a river wastes away and dries up,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so a man lies down and rises not again;till the heavens are no more
        he will not awakeor be roused out of his sleep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Oh that you would hide me in Sheol,that you would conceal me until
        your wrath be past,that you would appoint me a set time, and remember me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If a man dies, shall he live again?All the days of my service I would
        wait,till my renewal[[COMMENT(0)]] should come.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You would call, and I would answer you;you would long for the work
        of your hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For then you would number my steps;you would not keep watch over
        my sin;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'my transgression would be sealed up in a bag,and you would cover
        over my iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut the mountain falls and crumbles away,and the rock is removed
        from its place;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the waters wear away the stones;the torrents wash away the soil of
        the earth;so you destroy the hope of man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You prevail forever against him, and he passes;you change his countenance,
        and send him away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'His sons come to honor, and he does not know it;they are brought
        low, and he perceives it not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He feels only the pain of his own body,and he mourns only for himself.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz Accuses: Job Does Not Fear God'
      title: 'Eliphaz Accuses: Job Does Not Fear God'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShould a wise man answer with windy knowledge,and fill his
        belly with the east wind?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Should he argue in unprofitable talk,or in words with which he can
        do no good?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But you are doing away with the fear of God[[COMMENT(0)]]and hindering
        meditation before God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For your iniquity teaches your mouth,and you choose the tongue of
        the crafty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your own mouth condemns you, and not I;  your own lips testify against
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CAre you the first man who was born?Or were you brought forth
        before the hills?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Have you listened in the council of God?And do you limit wisdom to
        yourself?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  What do you know that we do not know?What do you understand that
        is not clear to us?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Both the gray-haired and the aged are among us,older than your
        father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Are the comforts of God too small for you,or the word that deals
        gently with you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Why does your heart carry you away,and why do your eyes flash,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'that you turn your spirit against Godand bring such words out of
        your mouth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  What is man, that he can be pure?Or he who is born of a woman,
        that he can be righteous?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Behold, God[[COMMENT(0)]]  puts no trust in his holy ones,and the
        heavens are not pure in his sight;  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:15 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  how much less one who is abominable and corrupt,a man who drinks
        injustice like water!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CI will show you; hear me,and what I have seen I will declare  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '(what wise men have told,without hiding it from their fathers,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'to whom alone the land was given,and no stranger passed among them).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The wicked man writhes in pain all his days,through all the years
        that are laid up for the ruthless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Dreadful sounds are in his ears;in prosperity the destroyer will
        come upon him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He does not believe that he will return out of darkness,and he is
        marked for the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He wanders abroad for bread, saying, \u2018Where is it?\u2019He knows
        that a day of darkness is ready at his hand;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'distress and anguish terrify him;they prevail against him, like a
        king ready for battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Because he has stretched out his hand against Godand defies the Almighty,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  running stubbornly against himwith a thickly bossed shield;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'because he has covered his face with his fatand gathered fat upon
        his waist  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and has lived in desolate cities,in houses that none should inhabit,which
        were ready to become heaps of ruins;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'he will not be rich, and his wealth will not endure,nor will his
        possessions spread over the earth;[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:29 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'he will not depart from darkness;the flame will dry up his shoots,and
        by the breath of his mouth he will depart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Let him not trust in emptiness, deceiving himself,for emptiness will
        be his payment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'It will be paid in full before his time,and his branch will not be
        green.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He will shake off his unripe grape like the vine,and cast off his
        blossom like the olive tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For the company of the godless is barren,and fire consumes the tents
        of bribery.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "They conceive trouble and give birth to evil,and their womb prepares
        deceit.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Replies: Miserable Comforters Are You'
      title: 'Job Replies: Miserable Comforters Are You'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI have heard many such things;  miserable comforters are you
        all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shall windy words have an end?Or what provokes you that you answer?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I also could speak as you do,if you were in my place;I could join
        words together against youand shake my head at you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I could strengthen you with my mouth,and the solace of my lips would
        assuage your pain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf I speak, my pain is not assuaged,and if I forbear, how much
        of it leaves me?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Surely now God has worn me out;  he has[[COMMENT(0)]] made desolate
        all my company.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:7 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 8
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he has shriveled me up,which is a witness against me,and my leanness
        has risen up against me;it testifies to my face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He has torn me in his wrath and hated me;he has gnashed his teeth
        at me;my adversary sharpens his eyes against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Men have gaped at me with their mouth;they have struck me insolently
        on the cheek;they mass themselves together against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'God gives me up to the ungodlyand casts me into the hands of the
        wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I was at ease, and he broke me apart;he seized me by the neck and
        dashed me to pieces;he set me up as his target;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'his archers surround me.He slashes open my kidneys and does not spare;he
        pours out my gall on the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He breaks me with breach upon breach;he runs upon me like a warrior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I have sewed sackcloth upon my skinand have laid my strength in the
        dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'My face is red with weeping,and on my eyelids is deep darkness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'although there is no violence in my hands,and my prayer is pure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CO earth, cover not my blood,and let my cry find no resting
        place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Even now, behold, my witness is in heaven,and he who testifies for
        me is on high.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My friends scorn me;my eye pours out tears to God,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'that he would argue the case of a man with God,as[[COMMENT(0)]] a
        son of man does with his neighbor.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:21 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For when a few years have comeI shall go the way from which I shall
        not return.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues: Where Then Is My Hope?'
      title: 'Job Continues: Where Then Is My Hope?'
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CMy spirit is broken; my days are extinct;  the graveyard
        is ready for me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Surely there are mockers about me,and my eye dwells on their provocation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLay down a pledge for me with you;who is there who will put
        up security for me?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Since you have closed their hearts to understanding,therefore you
        will not let them triumph.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He who informs against his friends to get a share of their property\u2014the
        eyes of his children will fail.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CHe has made me a byword of the peoples,and I am one before
        whom men spit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'My eye has grown dim from vexation,and all my members are like a
        shadow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The upright are appalled at this,and the innocent stirs himself up
        against the godless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Yet the righteous holds to his way,and he who has clean hands grows
        stronger and stronger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But you, come on again, all of you,and I shall not find a wise man
        among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My days are past; my plans are broken off,the desires of my heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They make night into day:\u2018The light,\u2019 they say, \u2018is
        near to the darkness.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:12 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If I hope for Sheol as my house,if I make my bed in darkness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "if I say to the pit, \u2018You are my father,\u2019and to the worm,
        \u2018My mother,\u2019 or \u2018My sister,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'where then is my hope?Who will see my hope?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Will it go down to the bars of Sheol?Shall we descend together into
        the dust?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: '17:16 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad Speaks: God Punishes the Wicked'
      title: 'Bildad Speaks: God Punishes the Wicked'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you hunt for words?Consider, and then we will
        speak.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Why are we counted as cattle?Why are we stupid in your sight?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You who tear yourself in your anger,shall the earth be forsaken for
        you,or the rock be removed out of its place?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIndeed, the light of the wicked is put out,and the flame of
        his fire does not shine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The light is dark in his tent,and his lamp above him is put out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'His strong steps are shortened,and his own schemes throw him down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For he is cast into a net by his own feet,and he walks on its mesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  A trap seizes him by the heel;a snare lays hold of him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'A rope is hidden for him in the ground,a trap for him in the path.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Terrors frighten him on every side,and chase him at his heels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'His strength is famished,and calamity is ready for his stumbling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'It consumes the parts of his skin;  the firstborn of death consumes
        his limbs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He is torn from the tent in which he trustedand is brought to the
        king of terrors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In his tent dwells that which is none of his;  sulfur is scattered
        over his habitation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'His roots dry up beneath,and his branches wither above.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'His memory perishes from the earth,and he has no name in the street.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  He is thrust from light into darkness,and driven out of the world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He has no posterity or progeny among his people,and no survivor where
        he used to live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They of the west are appalled at his day,and horror seizes them of
        the east.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Surely such are the dwellings of the unrighteous,such is the place
        of him who knows not God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Replies: My Redeemer Lives'
      title: 'Job Replies: My Redeemer Lives'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you torment meand break me in pieces with words?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'These ten times you have cast reproach upon me;are you not ashamed
        to wrong me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And even if it be true that I have erred,my error remains with myself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If indeed you magnify yourselves against meand make my disgrace an
        argument against me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'know then that God has put me in the wrongand closed his net about
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Behold, I cry out, \u2018Violence!\u2019 but I am not answered;I
        call for help, but there is no justice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He has walled up my way, so that I cannot pass,and he has set darkness
        upon my paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He has stripped from me my gloryand taken the crown from my head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He breaks me down on every side, and I am gone,and my hope has he
        pulled up like a tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He has kindled his wrath against meand counts me as his adversary.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'His troops come on together;they have cast up their siege ramp[[COMMENT(0)]]
        against meand encamp around my tent.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CHe has put my brothers far from me,and those who knew me are
        wholly estranged from me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'My relatives have failed me,my close friends have forgotten me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The guests in my house and my maidservants count me as a stranger;I
        have become a foreigner in their eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I call to my servant, but he gives me no answer;I must plead with
        him with my mouth for mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My breath is strange to my wife,and I am a stench to the children
        of my own mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Even young children despise me;when I rise they talk against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'All my intimate friends abhor me,and those whom I loved have turned
        against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My bones stick to my skin and to my flesh,and I have escaped by the
        skin of my teeth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Have mercy on me, have mercy on me, O you my friends,for the hand
        of God has touched me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Why do you, like God, pursue me?Why are you not satisfied with my
        flesh?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201COh that my words were written!Oh that they were inscribed in
        a book!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Oh that with an iron pen and leadthey were engraved in the rock forever!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For I know that my Redeemer lives,and at the last he will stand upon
        the earth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:25 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And after my skin has been thus destroyed,yet in[[COMMENT(0)]] my
        flesh I shall see God,  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:26 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'whom I shall see for myself,and my eyes shall behold, and not another.My
        heart faints within me!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "If you say, \u2018How we will pursue him!\u2019and, \u2018The root
        of the matter is found in him,\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:28 '
        content: 'Many Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "be afraid of the sword,for wrath brings the punishment of the sword,that
        you may know there is a judgment.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zophar Speaks: The Wicked Will Suffer'
      title: 'Zophar Speaks: The Wicked Will Suffer'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTherefore my thoughts answer me,because of my haste within
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I hear censure that insults me,and out of my understanding a spirit
        answers me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Do you not know this from of old,  since man was placed on earth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  that the exulting of the wicked is short,and the joy of the godless
        but for a moment?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Though his height mount up to the heavens,and his head reach to
        the clouds,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "he will perish forever like his own dung;those who have seen him
        will say, \u2018Where is he?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He will fly away like a dream and not be found;he will be chased
        away like a vision of the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  The eye that saw him will see him no more,nor will his place any
        more behold him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His children will seek the favor of the poor,and his hands will give
        back his wealth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'His bones are full of his youthful vigor,but it will lie down with
        him in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThough evil is sweet in his mouth,though he hides it under
        his tongue,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'though he is loath to let it goand holds it in his mouth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'yet his food is turned in his stomach;it is the venom of cobras within
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He swallows down riches and vomits them up again;God casts them out
        of his belly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He will suck the poison of cobras;  the tongue of a viper will kill
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He will not look upon the rivers,the streams flowing with honey and
        curds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He will give back the fruit of his toiland will not swallow it down;from
        the profit of his tradinghe will get no enjoyment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For he has crushed and abandoned the poor;he has seized a house that
        he did not build.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBecause he knew no contentment in his belly,  he will not let
        anything in which he delights escape him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'There was nothing left after he had eaten;therefore his prosperity
        will not endure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In the fullness of his sufficiency he will be in distress;the hand
        of everyone in misery will come against him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'To fill his belly to the full,God[[COMMENT(0)]] will send his burning
        anger against himand rain it upon him into his body.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:23 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  He will flee from an iron weapon;  a bronze arrow will strike him
        through.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'It is drawn forth and comes out of his body;  the glittering point
        comes out of his gallbladder;  terrors come upon him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Utter darkness is laid up for his treasures;  a fire not fanned will
        devour him;what is left in his tent will be consumed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  The heavens will reveal his iniquity,and the earth will rise up
        against him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The possessions of his house will be carried away,dragged off in
        the day of God\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]] wrath.  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:28 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  This is the wicked man\u2019s portion from God,  the heritage decreed
        for him by God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Replies: The Wicked Do Prosper'
      title: 'Job Replies: The Wicked Do Prosper'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CKeep listening to my words,and let this be your comfort.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Bear with me, and I will speak,and after I have spoken, mock on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As for me, is my complaint against man?Why should I not be impatient?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Look at me and be appalled,and lay your hand over your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When I remember, I am dismayed,and shuddering seizes my flesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Why do the wicked live,reach old age, and grow mighty in power?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their offspring are established in their presence,and their descendants
        before their eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Their houses are safe from fear,and no rod of God is upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Their bull breeds without fail;their cow calves and does not miscarry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They send out their little boys like a flock,and their children dance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They sing to the tambourine and the lyreand rejoice to the sound
        of the pipe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They spend their days in prosperity,and in peace they go down to
        Sheol.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They say to God, \u2018Depart from us!We do not desire the knowledge
        of your ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  What is the Almighty, that we should serve him?And what profit
        do we get if we pray to him?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Behold, is not their prosperity in their hand?  The counsel of the
        wicked is far from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CHow often is it that the lamp of the wicked is put out?That
        their calamity comes upon them?That God[[COMMENT(0)]] distributes pains in
        his anger?  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'That they are like straw before the wind,and like chaff that the
        storm carries away?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You say, \u2018God stores up their iniquity for their children.\u2019Let
        him pay it out to them, that they may know it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Let their own eyes see their destruction,and let them drink of the
        wrath of the Almighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For what do they care for their houses after them,when the number
        of their months is cut off?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Will any teach God knowledge,seeing that he judges those who are
        on high?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'One dies in his full vigor,being wholly at ease and secure,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'his pails[[COMMENT(0)]] full of milkand the marrow of his bones moist.  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:24 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Another dies in bitterness of soul,never having tasted of prosperity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They lie down alike in the dust,and the worms cover them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBehold, I know your thoughtsand your schemes to wrong me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For you say, \u2018Where is the house of the prince?Where is the
        tent in which the wicked lived?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Have you not asked those who travel the roads,and do you not accept
        their testimony  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'that the evil man is spared in the day of calamity,that he is rescued
        in the day of wrath?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Who declares his way to his face,and who repays him for what he has
        done?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When he is carried to the grave,watch is kept over his tomb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  The clods of the valley are sweet to him;  all mankind follows
        after him,and those who go before him are innumerable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "How then will you comfort me with empty nothings?There is nothing
        left of your answers but falsehood.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Eliphaz Speaks: Job\u2019s Wickedness Is Great"
      title: "Eliphaz Speaks: Job\u2019s Wickedness Is Great"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CCan a man be profitable to God?Surely he who is wise is profitable
        to himself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is it any pleasure to the Almighty if you are in the right,or is
        it gain to him if you make your ways blameless?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Is it for your fear of him that he reproves youand enters into judgment
        with you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Is not your evil abundant?There is no end to your iniquities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For you have exacted pledges of your brothers for nothing  and stripped
        the naked of their clothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You have given no water to the weary to drink,and you have withheld
        bread from the hungry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The man with power possessed the land,and the favored man lived
        in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You have sent widows away empty,and the arms of the fatherless were
        crushed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore snares are all around you,and sudden terror overwhelms
        you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'or darkness, so that you cannot see,and a flood of water covers you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIs not God high in the heavens?See the highest stars, how lofty
        they are!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But you say, \u2018What does God know?Can he judge through the deep
        darkness?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  Thick clouds veil him, so that he does not see,and he walks on
        the vault of heaven.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Will you keep to the old waythat wicked men have trod?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They were snatched away before their time;their foundation was washed
        away.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:16 '
        content: Or (or )
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They said to God, \u2018Depart from us,\u2019and \u2018What can the
        Almighty do to us?\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Yet he filled their houses with good things\u2014but the counsel
        of the wicked is far from me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  The righteous see it and are glad;the innocent one mocks at them,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "saying, \u2018Surely our adversaries are cut off,and what they left
        the fire has consumed.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201CAgree with God, and be at peace;thereby good will come to
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Receive instruction from his mouth,and lay up his words in your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If you return to the Almighty you will be built up;if you remove
        injustice far from your tents,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'if you lay gold in the dust,and gold of Ophir among the stones of
        the torrent-bed,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then the Almighty will be your goldand your precious silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For then you will delight yourself in the Almightyand lift up your
        face to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You will make your prayer to him, and he will hear you,and you will
        pay your vows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You will decide on a matter, and it will be established for you,and
        light will shine on your ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For when they are humbled you say, \u2018It is because of pride\u2019;[[COMMENT(0)]]but
        he saves the lowly.  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:29 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He delivers even the one who is not innocent,who will be delivered
        through the cleanness of your hands.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Replies: Where Is God?'
      title: 'Job Replies: Where Is God?'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CToday also my complaint is bitter;[[COMMENT(0)]]my hand is
        heavy on account of my groaning.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Oh, that I knew where I might find him,that I might come even to
        his seat!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I would lay my case before himand fill my mouth with arguments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I would know what he would answer meand understand what he would
        say to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Would he contend with me in the greatness of his power?No; he would
        pay attention to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There an upright man could argue with him,and I would be acquitted
        forever by my judge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBehold, I go forward, but he is not there,and backward, but
        I do not perceive him;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'on the left hand when he is working, I do not behold him;he turns
        to the right hand, but I do not see him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But he knows the way that I take;when he has tried me, I shall come
        out as gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My foot has held fast to his steps;I have kept his way and have not
        turned aside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I have not departed from the commandment of his lips;I have treasured
        the words of his mouth more than my portion of food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But he is unchangeable,[[COMMENT(0)]] and who can turn him back?What
        he desires, that he does.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For he will complete what he appoints for me,and many such things
        are in his mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore I am terrified at his presence;when I consider, I am in
        dread of him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'God has made my heart faint;the Almighty has terrified me;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: yet I am not silenced because of the darkness,nor because thick darkness
        covers my face.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhy are not times of judgment kept by the Almighty,and why
        do those who know him never see his days?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Some move landmarks;they seize flocks and pasture them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They drive away the donkey of the fatherless;they take the widow\u2019s
        ox for a pledge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They thrust the poor off the road;the poor of the earth all hide
        themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Behold, like wild donkeys in the desertthe poor[[COMMENT(0)]]  go
        out to their toil, seeking game;the wasteland yields food for their children.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They gather their[[COMMENT(0)]] fodder in the field,and they glean
        the vineyard of the wicked man.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They lie all night naked, without clothing,and have no covering in
        the cold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They are wet with the rain of the mountainsand cling to the rock
        for lack of shelter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '(There are those who snatch the fatherless child from the breast,and
        they take a pledge against the poor.)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They go about naked, without clothing;hungry, they carry the sheaves;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'among the olive rows of the wicked[[COMMENT(0)]] they make oil;they
        tread the winepresses, but suffer thirst.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:11 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'From out of the city the dying[[COMMENT(0)]] groan,and the soul of
        the wounded cries for help;yet God charges no one with wrong.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThere are those who rebel against the light,who are not acquainted
        with its ways,and do not stay in its paths.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The murderer rises before it is light,that he may kill the poor and
        needy,and in the night he is like a thief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The eye of the adulterer also waits for the twilight,saying, \u2018No
        eye will see me\u2019;and he veils his face.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In the dark they dig through houses;by day they shut themselves up;they
        do not know the light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For deep darkness is morning to all of them;for they are friends
        with the terrors of deep darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou say, \u2018Swift are they on the face of the waters;their
        portion is cursed in the land;no treader turns toward their vineyards.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Drought and heat snatch away the snow waters;so does Sheol those
        who have sinned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The womb forgets them;the worm finds them sweet;they are no longer
        remembered,so wickedness is broken like a tree.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThey wrong the barren, childless woman,and do no good to the
        widow.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yet God[[COMMENT(0)]] prolongs the life of the mighty by his power;they
        rise up when they despair of life.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:22 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He gives them security, and they are supported,and his eyes are upon
        their ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They are exalted a little while, and then are gone;they are brought
        low and gathered up like all others;they are cut off like the heads of grain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If it is not so, who will prove me a liarand show that there is nothing
        in what I say?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad Speaks: Man Cannot Be Righteous'
      title: 'Bildad Speaks: Man Cannot Be Righteous'
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDominion and fear are with God;[[COMMENT(0)]]he makes peace
        in his high heaven.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is there any number to his armies?Upon whom does his light not arise?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'How then can man be in the right before God?How can he who is born
        of woman be pure?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Behold, even the moon is not bright,and the stars are not pure in
        his eyes;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  how much less man, who is a maggot,and the son of man, who is a
        worm!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job Replies: God\u2019s Majesty Is Unsearchable"
      title: "Job Replies: God\u2019s Majesty Is Unsearchable"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow you have helped him who has no power!How you have saved
        the arm that has no strength!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'How you have counseled him who has no wisdom,and plentifully declared
        sound knowledge!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'With whose help have you uttered words,and whose breath has come
        out from you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The dead trembleunder the waters and their inhabitants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Sheol is naked before God,[[COMMENT(0)]]and Abaddon has no covering.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He stretches out the north over the voidand hangs the earth on nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He binds up the waters in his thick clouds,and the cloud is not split
        open under them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He covers the face of the full moon[[COMMENT(0)]]and spreads over
        it his cloud.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He has inscribed a circle on the face of the watersat the boundary
        between light and darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  The pillars of heaven trembleand are astounded at his rebuke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'By his power he stilled the sea;by his understanding he shattered
        Rahab.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  By his wind the heavens were made fair;his hand pierced the fleeing
        serpent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Behold, these are but the outskirts of his ways,and how small a whisper
        do we hear of him!But the thunder of his power who can understand?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues: I Will Maintain My Integrity'
      title: 'Job Continues: I Will Maintain My Integrity'
      number: 1
      content: '  And Job again took up his discourse, and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAs God lives, who has taken away my right,and the Almighty,
        who has made my soul bitter,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'as long as my breath is in me,and the spirit of God is in my nostrils,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'my lips will not speak falsehood,and my tongue will not utter deceit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Far be it from me to say that you are right;till I die I will not
        put away my integrity from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I hold fast my righteousness and will not let it go;my heart does
        not reproach me for any of my days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CLet my enemy be as the wicked,and let him who rises up against
        me be as the unrighteous.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  For what is the hope of the godless when God cuts him off,when
        God takes away his life?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Will God hear his crywhen distress comes upon him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Will he take delight in the Almighty?Will he call upon God at all
        times?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I will teach you concerning the hand of God;  what is with the Almighty
        I will not conceal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Behold, all of you have seen it yourselves;why then have you become
        altogether vain?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CThis is the portion of a wicked man with God,and the heritage
        that oppressors receive from the Almighty:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If his children are multiplied, it is for the sword,and his descendants
        have not enough bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Those who survive him the pestilence buries,and his widows do not
        weep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Though he heap up silver like dust,and pile up clothing like clay,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'he may pile it up, but the righteous will wear it,and the innocent
        will divide the silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He builds his house like a moth\u2019s,like a booth that a watchman
        makes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He goes to bed rich, but will do so no more;he opens his eyes, and
        his wealth is gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Terrors overtake him like a flood;in the night a whirlwind carries
        him off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  The east wind lifts him up and he is gone;it sweeps him out of
        his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It[[COMMENT(0)]] hurls at him without pity;he flees from its power
        in headlong flight.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:22 '
        content: Or (that is, God); also verse 23Or ; also verse 23
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: It claps its hands at himand hisses at him from its place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues: Where Is Wisdom?'
      title: 'Job Continues: Where Is Wisdom?'
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CSurely there is a mine for silver,and a place for gold that
        they refine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Iron is taken out of the earth,and copper is smelted from the ore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Man puts an end to darknessand searches out to the farthest limitthe
        ore in gloom and deep darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He opens shafts in a valley away from where anyone lives;they are
        forgotten by travelers;they hang in the air, far away from mankind; they
        swing to and fro.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'As for the earth, out of it comes bread,but underneath it is turned
        up as by fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Its stones are the place of sapphires,[[COMMENT(0)]]and it has dust
        of gold.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:6 '
        content: Or ; also verse 16
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThat path no bird of prey knows,and the falcon\u2019s eye has
        not seen it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The proud beasts have not trodden it;  the lion has not passed
        over it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CMan puts his hand to the flinty rockand overturns mountains
        by the roots.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He cuts out channels in the rocks,and his eye sees every precious
        thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He dams up the streams so that they do not trickle,and the thing
        that is hidden he brings out to light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  \u201CBut where shall wisdom be found?And where is the place of
        understanding?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Man does not know its worth,and it is not found in the land of the
        living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  The deep says, \u2018It is not in me,\u2019and the sea says, \u2018It
        is not with me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'It cannot be bought for gold,and silver cannot be weighed as its
        price.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It cannot be valued in the gold of Ophir,in precious onyx or sapphire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Gold and glass cannot equal it,nor can it be exchanged for jewels
        of fine gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'No mention shall be made of coral or of crystal;the price of wisdom
        is above pearls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  The topaz of Ethiopia cannot equal it,nor can it be valued in pure
        gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFrom where, then, does wisdom come?And where is the place of
        understanding?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'It is hidden from the eyes of all livingand concealed from the birds
        of the air.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  Abaddon and Death say,\u2018We have heard a rumor of it with our
        ears.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  \u201CGod understands the way to it,and he knows its place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For he looks to the ends of the earthand sees everything under the
        heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When he gave to the wind its weightand apportioned the waters by
        measure,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'when he made a decree for the rainand a way for the lightning of
        the thunder,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'then he saw it and declared it;he established it, and searched it
        out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And he said to man,\u2018Behold, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom,and
        to turn away from evil is understanding.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Summary Defense"
      title: "Job\u2019s Summary Defense"
      number: 1
      content: '  And Job again took up his discourse, and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COh, that I were as in the months of old,as in the days when
        God watched over me,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'when his lamp shone upon my head,and by his light I walked through
        darkness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'as I was in my prime,[[COMMENT(0)]]when the friendship of God was
        upon my tent,  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'when the Almighty was yet with me,when my children were all around
        me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'when my steps were washed with butter,and the rock poured out for
        me streams of oil!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When I went out to the gate of the city,when I prepared my seat in
        the square,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the young men saw me and withdrew,and the aged rose and stood;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the princes refrained from talkingand laid their hand on their mouth;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the voice of the nobles was hushed,and their tongue stuck to the
        roof of their mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the ear heard, it called me blessed,and when the eye saw, it
        approved,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'because I delivered the poor who cried for help,and the fatherless
        who had none to help him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  The blessing of him who was about to perish came upon me,and I
        caused the widow\u2019s heart to sing for joy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I put on righteousness, and it clothed me;my justice was like a robe
        and a turban.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I was eyes to the blindand feet to the lame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I was a father to the needy,and I searched out the cause of him whom
        I did not know.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I broke the fangs of the unrighteousand made him drop his prey from
        his teeth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  Then I thought, \u2018I shall die in my nest,and I shall multiply
        my days as the sand,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'my roots spread out to the waters,with the dew all night on my branches,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "my glory fresh with me,and my bow ever new in my hand.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CMen listened to me and waitedand kept silence for my counsel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After I spoke they did not speak again,and my word dropped upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They waited for me as for the rain,and they opened their mouths as
        for the spring rain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I smiled on them when they had no confidence,and the light of my
        face they did not cast down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: I chose their way and sat as chief,and I lived like a king among his
        troops,like one who comforts mourners.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBut now they laugh at me,men who are younger than I,whose
        fathers I would have disdainedto set with the dogs of my flock.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'What could I gain from the strength of their hands,  men whose vigor
        is gone?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Through want and hard hungerthey gnaw the dry ground by night in
        waste and desolation;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'they pick saltwort and the leaves of bushes,and the roots of the
        broom tree for their food.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  They are driven out from human company;they shout after them as
        after a thief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In the gullies of the torrents they must dwell,in holes of the earth
        and of the rocks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Among the bushes they bray;under the nettles they huddle together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'A senseless, a nameless brood,they have been whipped out of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd now I have become their song;I am a byword to them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They abhor me; they keep aloof from me;they do not hesitate to spit
        at the sight of me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Because God has loosed my cord and humbled me,they have cast off
        restraint[[COMMENT(0)]] in my presence.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:11 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On my right hand the rabble rise;they push away my feet;they cast
        up against me their ways of destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They break up my path;they promote my calamity;they need no one to
        help them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As through a wide breach they come;amid the crash they roll on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Terrors are turned upon me;my honor is pursued as by the wind,and
        my prosperity has passed away like a cloud.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd now my soul is poured out within me;days of affliction
        have taken hold of me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  The night racks my bones,and the pain that gnaws me takes no rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'With great force my garment is disfigured;it binds me about like
        the collar of my tunic.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'God[[COMMENT(0)]] has cast me into the mire,and I have become like
        dust and ashes.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I cry to you for help and you do not answer me;I stand, and you only
        look at me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You have turned cruel to me;with the might of your hand you persecute
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  You lift me up on the wind; you make me ride on it,and you toss
        me about in the roar of the storm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  For I know that you will bring me to deathand to the house appointed
        for all living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CYet does not one in a heap of ruins stretch out his hand,and
        in his disaster cry for help?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:24 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Did not I weep for him whose day was hard?Was not my soul grieved
        for the needy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But when I hoped for good, evil came,and when I waited for light,
        darkness came.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'My inward parts are in turmoil and never still;days of affliction
        come to meet me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'I go about darkened, but not by the sun;I stand up in the assembly
        and cry for help.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I am a brother of jackalsand a companion of ostriches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'My skin turns black and falls from me,and my bones burn with heat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: My lyre is turned to mourning,and my pipe to the voice of those who
        weep.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Final Appeal"
      title: "Job\u2019s Final Appeal"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CI have made a covenant with my eyes;how then could I gaze
        at a virgin?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'What would be my portion from God aboveand my heritage from the Almighty
        on high?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is not calamity for the unrighteous,and disaster for the workers
        of iniquity?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Does not he see my waysand number all my steps?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf I have walked with falsehoodand my foot has hastened to
        deceit;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(Let me be weighed in a just balance,and let God know my integrity!)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'if my step has turned aside from the wayand my heart has gone after
        my eyes,and if any spot has stuck to my hands,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'then let me sow, and another eat,and let what grows for me[[COMMENT(0)]]
        be rooted out.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIf my heart has been enticed toward a woman,and I have lain
        in wait at my neighbor\u2019s door,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'then let my wife grind for another,and let others bow down on her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For that would be a heinous crime;that would be an iniquity to be
        punished by the judges;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'for that would be a fire that consumes as far as Abaddon,and it would
        burn to the root all my increase.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf I have rejected the cause of my manservant or my maidservant,when
        they brought a complaint against me,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'what then shall I do when God rises up?When he makes inquiry, what
        shall I answer him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Did not he who made me in the womb make him?And did not one fashion
        us in the womb?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf I have withheld anything that the poor desired,or have caused
        the eyes of the widow to fail,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'or have eaten my morsel alone,and the fatherless has not eaten of
        it  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "(for from my youth the fatherless[[COMMENT(0)]] grew up with me as
        with a father,and from my mother\u2019s womb I guided the widow),  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'if I have seen anyone perish for lack of clothing,or the needy without
        covering,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'if his body has not blessed me,[[COMMENT(0)]]and if he was not warmed
        with the fleece of my sheep,  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:20 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'if I have raised my hand against the fatherless,because I saw my
        help in the gate,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'then let my shoulder blade fall from my shoulder,and let my arm be
        broken from its socket.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For I was in terror of calamity from God,and I could not have faced
        his majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  \u201CIf I have made gold my trustor called fine gold my confidence,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'if I have rejoiced because my wealth was abundantor because my hand
        had found much,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  if I have looked at the sun[[COMMENT(0)]] when it shone,or the
        moon moving in splendor,  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:26 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and my heart has been secretly enticed,and my mouth has kissed my
        hand,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'this also would be an iniquity to be punished by the judges,for I
        would have been false to God above.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIf I have rejoiced at the ruin of him who hated me,or exulted
        when evil overtook him  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '(I have not let my mouth sinby asking for his life with a curse),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "if the men of my tent have not said,\u2018Who is there that has not
        been filled with his meat?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '(the sojourner has not lodged in the street;I have opened my doors
        to the traveler),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'if I have concealed my transgressions as others do[[COMMENT(0)]]by
        hiding my iniquity in my heart,  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:33 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "because I stood in great fear of the multitude,and the contempt of
        families terrified me,so that I kept silence, and did not go out of doors\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Oh, that I had one to hear me!(Here is my signature! Let the Almighty
        answer me!)Oh, that I had the indictment written by my adversary!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Surely I would carry it on my shoulder;I would bind it on me as a
        crown;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'I would give him an account of all my steps;like a prince I would
        approach him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CIf my land has cried out against meand its furrows have wept
        together,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '  if I have eaten its yield without paymentand made its owners breathe
        their last,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "let thorns grow instead of wheat,and foul weeds instead of barley.\u201DThe
        words of Job are ended."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Rebukes Job\u2019s Three Friends"
      title: "Elihu Rebukes Job\u2019s Three Friends"
      number: 1
      content: '  So these three men ceased to answer Job, because he was righteous
        in his own eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite, of the family of Ram,
        burned with anger. He burned with anger at Job because he justified himself
        rather than God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He burned with anger also at Job\u2019s three friends because they
        had found no answer, although they had declared Job to be in the wrong. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Elihu had waited to speak to Job because they were older than
        he. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when Elihu saw that there was no answer in the mouth of these
        three men, he burned with anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite answered and said:\u201CI
        am young in years,and you are aged;therefore I was timid and afraidto declare
        my opinion to you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I said, \u2018Let days speak,and many years teach wisdom.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But it is the spirit in man,  the breath of the Almighty, that makes
        him understand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  It is not the old[[COMMENT(0)]] who are wise,nor the aged who understand
        what is right.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:9 '
        content: Hebrew [in years]
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore I say, \u2018Listen to me;let me also declare my opinion.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBehold, I waited for your words,I listened for your wise sayings,while
        you searched out what to say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I gave you my attention,and, behold, there was none among you who
        refuted Jobor who answered his words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Beware lest you say, \u2018We have found wisdom;God may vanquish
        him, not a man.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He has not directed his words against me,and I will not answer him
        with your speeches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThey are dismayed; they answer no more;they have not a word
        to say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And shall I wait, because they do not speak,because they stand there,
        and answer no more?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I also will answer with my share;I also will declare my opinion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For I am full of words;the spirit within me constrains me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, my belly is like wine that has no vent;like new wineskins
        ready to burst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  I must speak, that I may find relief;I must open my lips and answer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I will not show partiality to any manor use flattery toward any person.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For I do not know how to flatter,else my Maker would soon take me
        away.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Rebukes Job'
      title: Elihu Rebukes Job
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBut now, hear my speech, O Job,and listen to all my words.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Behold, I open my mouth;the tongue in my mouth speaks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'My words declare the uprightness of my heart,and what my lips know
        they speak sincerely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  The Spirit of God has made me,and the breath of the Almighty gives
        me life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Answer me, if you can;  set your words in order before me; take
        your stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, I am toward God as you are;I too was pinched off from a piece
        of clay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Behold, no fear of me need terrify you;my pressure will not be heavy
        upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CSurely you have spoken in my ears,and I have heard the sound
        of your words.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You say, \u2018I am pure, without transgression;I am clean, and there
        is no iniquity in me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Behold, he finds occasions against me,he counts me as his enemy,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "he puts my feet in the stocksand watches all my paths.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBehold, in this you are not right. I will answer you,for God
        is greater than man.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Why do you contend against him,saying, \u2018He will answer none
        of man\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]] words\u2019?  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For God speaks in one way,  and in two, though man does not perceive
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In a dream, in a vision of the night,when deep sleep falls on men,while
        they slumber on their beds,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then he opens the ears of menand terrifies[[COMMENT(0)]] them with
        warnings,  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'that he may turn man aside from his deedand conceal pride from a
        man;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'he keeps back his soul from the pit,his life from perishing by the
        sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CMan is also rebuked with pain on his bedand with continual
        strife in his bones,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'so that his life loathes bread,and his appetite the choicest food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'His flesh is so wasted away that it cannot be seen,and his bones
        that were not seen stick out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'His soul draws near the pit,and his life to those who bring death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If there be for him an angel,  a mediator, one of the thousand,to
        declare to man what is right for him,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and he is merciful to him, and says,\u2018Deliver him from going
        down into the pit;I have found a ransom;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "let his flesh become fresh with youth;let him return to the days
        of his youthful vigor\u2019;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'then man[[COMMENT(0)]]  prays to God, and he accepts him;he sees
        his face with a shout of joy,and he restores to man his righteousness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:26 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He sings before men and says:\u2018I sinned and perverted what was
        right,and it was not repaid to me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "He has redeemed my soul from going down into the pit,and my life
        shall look upon the light.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CBehold, God does all these things,twice, three times, with
        a man,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'to bring back his soul from the pit,that he may be lighted with the
        light of life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Pay attention, O Job, listen to me;be silent, and I will speak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'If you have any words, answer me;  speak, for I desire to justify
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "If not, listen to me;be silent, and I will teach you wisdom.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Asserts God\u2019s Justice"
      title: "Elihu Asserts God\u2019s Justice"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Elihu answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHear my words, you wise men,and give ear to me, you who know;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'for the ear tests wordsas the palate tastes food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let us choose what is right;let us know among ourselves what is good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For Job has said, \u2018I am in the right,and God has taken away
        my right;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "in spite of my right I am counted a liar;my wound is incurable, though
        I am without transgression.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'What man is like Job,who drinks up scoffing like water,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'who travels in company with evildoersand walks with wicked men?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For he has said, \u2018It profits a man nothingthat he should take
        delight in God.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTherefore, hear me, you men of understanding:far be it from
        God that he should do wickedness,and from the Almighty that he should do
        wrong.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For according to the work of a man he will repay him,and according
        to his ways he will make it befall him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Of a truth, God will not do wickedly,and the Almighty will not pervert
        justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who gave him charge over the earth,and who laid on him[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the whole world?  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If he should set his heart to itand gather to himself his spirit
        and his breath,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'all flesh would perish together,and man would return to dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf you have understanding, hear this;listen to what I say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Shall one who hates justice govern?Will you condemn him who is
        righteous and mighty,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "who says to a king, \u2018Worthless one,\u2019and to nobles, \u2018Wicked
        man,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'who shows no partiality to princes,nor regards the rich more than
        the poor,for they are all the work of his hands?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In a moment they die;at midnight the people are shaken and pass away,and
        the mighty are taken away by no human hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CFor his eyes are on the ways of a man,and he sees all his steps.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'There is no gloom or deep darknesswhere evildoers may hide themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For God[[COMMENT(0)]] has no need to consider a man further,that
        he should go before God in judgment.  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:23 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He shatters the mighty without investigationand sets others in their
        place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Thus, knowing their works,he overturns them in the night, and they
        are crushed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He strikes them for their wickednessin a place for all to see,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'because they turned aside from following himand had no regard for
        any of his ways,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "so that they caused the cry of the poor to come to him,and he heard
        the cry of the afflicted\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When he is quiet, who can condemn?When he hides his face, who can
        behold him,whether it be a nation or a man?\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'that a godless man should not reign,that he should not ensnare the
        people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CFor has anyone said to God,\u2018I have borne punishment; I
        will not offend any more;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "  teach me what I do not see;if I have done iniquity, I will do it
        no more\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Will he then make repayment to suit you,because you reject it?For
        you must choose, and not I;therefore declare what you know.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:33 '
        content: "The meaning of the Hebrew in verses 29\u201333 is uncertain"
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Men of understanding will say to me,and the wise man who hears me
        will say:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018Job speaks without knowledge;his words are without insight.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Would that Job were tried to the end,because he answers like wicked
        men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For he adds rebellion to his sin;he claps his hands among usand multiplies
        his words against God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Condemns Job'
      title: Elihu Condemns Job
      number: 1
      content: '  And Elihu answered and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDo you think this to be just?Do you say, \u2018It is my right
        before God,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "that you ask, \u2018What advantage have I?How am I better off than
        if I had sinned?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will answer youand your friends with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Look at the heavens, and see;and behold the clouds, which are higher
        than you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'If you have sinned, what do you accomplish against him?And if your
        transgressions are multiplied, what do you do to him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  If you are righteous, what do you give to him?Or what does he receive
        from your hand?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Your wickedness concerns a man like yourself,and your righteousness
        a son of man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBecause of the multitude of oppressions people cry out;they
        call for help because of the arm of the mighty.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '35:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But none says, \u2018Where is God my Maker,who gives songs in the
        night,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "who teaches us more than the beasts of the earthand makes us wiser
        than the birds of the heavens?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'There they cry out, but he does not answer,because of the pride of
        evil men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Surely God does not hear an empty cry,nor does the Almighty regard
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'How much less when you say that you do not see him,that the case
        is before him, and you are waiting for him!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And now, because his anger does not punish,and he does not take much
        note of transgression,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '35:15 '
        content: Theodotion, Symmachus (compare Vulgate); the meaning of the Hebrew
          word is uncertain
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Job opens his mouth in empty talk;he multiplies words without knowledge.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Extols God\u2019s Greatness"
      title: "Elihu Extols God\u2019s Greatness"
      number: 1
      content: '  And Elihu continued, and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBear with me a little, and I will show you,for I have yet something
        to say on God\u2019s behalf.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I will get my knowledge from afarand ascribe righteousness to my
        Maker.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For truly my words are not false;one who is perfect in knowledge
        is with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBehold, God is mighty, and does not despise any;he is mighty
        in strength of understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He does not keep the wicked alive,but gives the afflicted their right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He does not withdraw his eyes from the righteous,but with kings on
        the thronehe sets them forever, and they are exalted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And if they are bound in chainsand caught in the cords of affliction,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'then he declares to them their workand their transgressions, that
        they are behaving arrogantly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He opens their ears to instructionand commands that they return from
        iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  If they listen and serve him,they complete their days in prosperity,and
        their years in pleasantness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But if they do not listen, they perish by the swordand die without
        knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThe godless in heart cherish anger;they do not cry for help
        when he binds them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They die in youth,and their life ends among the cult prostitutes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He delivers the afflicted by their afflictionand opens their ear
        by adversity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He also allured you out of distressinto a broad place where there
        was no cramping,and what was set on your table was full of fatness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut you are full of the judgment on the wicked;judgment and
        justice seize you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Beware lest wrath entice you into scoffing,and let not the greatness
        of the ransom turn you aside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Will your cry for help avail to keep you from distress,or all the
        force of your strength?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do not long for the night,when peoples vanish in their place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Take care; do not turn to iniquity,for this you have chosen rather
        than affliction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Behold, God is exalted in his power;who is a teacher like him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Who has prescribed for him his way,or who can say, \u2018You have
        done wrong\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CRemember to extol his work,of which men have sung.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'All mankind has looked on it;man beholds it from afar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Behold, God is great, and we know him not;the number of his years
        is unsearchable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For he draws up the drops of water;they distill his mist in rain,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'which the skies pour downand drop on mankind abundantly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Can anyone understand the spreading of the clouds,the thunderings
        of his pavilion?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Behold, he scatters his lightning about himand covers the roots of
        the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For by these he judges peoples;he gives food in abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He covers his hands with the lightningand commands it to strike the
        mark.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Its crashing declares his presence;[[COMMENT(0)]]the cattle also declare
        that he rises.
      comments:
      - number: '36:33 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Proclaims God\u2019s Majesty"
      title: "Elihu Proclaims God\u2019s Majesty"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt this also my heart tremblesand leaps out of its place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Keep listening to the thunder of his voiceand the rumbling that comes
        from his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Under the whole heaven he lets it go,and his lightning to the corners
        of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After it his voice roars;  he thunders with his majestic voice,and
        he does not restrain the lightnings[[COMMENT(0)]] when his voice is heard.  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'God thunders wondrously with his voice;he does great things that
        we cannot comprehend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For to the snow he says, \u2018Fall on the earth,\u2019likewise to
        the downpour, his mighty downpour.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He seals up the hand of every man,that all men whom he made may know
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the beasts go into their lairs,and remain in their dens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'From its chamber comes the whirlwind,and cold from the scattering
        winds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'By the breath of God ice is given,and the broad waters are frozen
        fast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He loads the thick cloud with moisture;the clouds scatter his lightning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They turn around and around by his guidance,  to accomplish all that
        he commands themon the face of the habitable world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whether for correction or for his landor for love, he causes it to
        happen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CHear this, O Job;stop and consider the wondrous works of God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Do you know how God lays his command upon themand causes the lightning
        of his cloud to shine?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do you know the balancings[[COMMENT(0)]] of the clouds,the wondrous
        works of him who is perfect in knowledge,  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'you whose garments are hotwhen the earth is still because of the
        south wind?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Can you, like him, spread out the skies,hard as a cast metal mirror?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Teach us what we shall say to him;we cannot draw up our case because
        of darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Shall it be told him that I would speak?Did a man ever wish that
        he would be swallowed up?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAnd now no one looks on the lightwhen it is bright in the skies,when
        the wind has passed and cleared them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Out of the north comes golden splendor;God is clothed with awesome
        majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The Almighty\u2014we cannot find him;he is great in power;  justice
        and abundant righteousness he will not violate.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore men fear him;he does not regard any who are wise in their
        own conceit.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: '37:24 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Answers Job'
      title: The  Answers Job
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        answered Job out of the whirlwind and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWho is this that darkens counsel by words without knowledge?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Dress for action[[COMMENT(0)]] like a man;I will question you,
        and you make it known to me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhere were you when I laid the foundation of the earth?Tell
        me, if you have understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Who determined its measurements\u2014surely you know!Or who stretched
        the line upon it?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On what were its bases sunk,or who laid its cornerstone,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'when the morning stars sang togetherand all the sons of God shouted
        for joy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201COr who shut in the sea with doorswhen it burst out from the
        womb,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'when I made clouds its garmentand thick darkness its swaddling band,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and prescribed limits for itand set bars and doors,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and said, \u2018Thus far shall you come, and no farther,and here
        shall your proud waves be stayed\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHave you commanded the morning since your days began,and caused
        the dawn to know its place,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'that it might take hold of the skirts of the earth,and the wicked
        be shaken out of it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'It is changed like clay under the seal,and its features stand out
        like a garment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'From the wicked their light is withheld,and their uplifted arm is
        broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CHave you entered into the springs of the sea,or walked in the
        recesses of the deep?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Have the gates of death been revealed to you,or have you seen the
        gates of deep darkness?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Have you comprehended the expanse of the earth?Declare, if you know
        all this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhere is the way to the dwelling of light,and where is the
        place of darkness,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'that you may take it to its territoryand that you may discern the
        paths to its home?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You know, for you were born then,and the number of your days is great!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CHave you entered the storehouses of the snow,or have you seen
        the storehouses of the hail,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'which I have reserved for the time of trouble,  for the day of battle
        and war?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'What is the way to the place where the light is distributed,or where
        the east wind is scattered upon the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWho has cleft a channel for the torrents of rainand a way for
        the thunderbolt,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'to bring rain on a land where no man is,on the desert in which there
        is no man,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'to satisfy the waste and desolate land,and to make the ground sprout
        with grass?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CHas the rain a father,or who has begotten the drops of dew?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From whose womb did the ice come forth,and who has given birth to
        the frost of heaven?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The waters become hard like stone,and the face of the deep is frozen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CCan you bind the chains of the Pleiadesor loose the cords of
        Orion?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Can you lead forth the Mazzaroth[[COMMENT(0)]] in their season,or
        can you guide the Bear with its children?  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:32 '
        content: Probably the name of a constellation
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Do you know the ordinances of the heavens?Can you establish their
        rule on the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CCan you lift up your voice to the clouds,that a flood of waters
        may cover you?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Can you send forth lightnings, that they may goand say to you, \u2018Here
        we are\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Who has put wisdom in the inward parts[[COMMENT(0)]]or given understanding
        to the mind?  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:36 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Who can number the clouds by wisdom?Or who can tilt the waterskins
        of the heavens,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'when the dust runs into a massand the clods stick fast together?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CCan you hunt the prey for the lion,or satisfy the appetite
        of the young lions,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'when they crouch in their densor lie in wait in their thicket?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: Who provides for the raven its prey,when its young ones cry to God
        for help,and wander about for lack of food?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CDo you know when the mountain goats give birth?Do you observe
        the calving of the does?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Can you number the months that they fulfill,and do you know the time
        when they give birth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'when they crouch, bring forth their offspring,and are delivered of
        their young?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Their young ones become strong; they grow up in the open;they go
        out and do not return to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWho has let the wild donkey go free?Who has loosed the bonds
        of the swift donkey,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'to whom I have given the arid plain for his homeand the salt land
        for his dwelling place?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He scorns the tumult of the city;he hears not the shouts of the driver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He ranges the mountains as his pasture,and he searches after every
        green thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIs the wild ox willing to serve you?Will he spend the night
        at your manger?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Can you bind him in the furrow with ropes,or will he harrow the valleys
        after you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Will you depend on him because his strength is great,and will you
        leave to him your labor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Do you have faith in him that he will return your grainand gather
        it to your threshing floor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThe wings of the ostrich wave proudly,but are they the pinions
        and plumage of love?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '39:13 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For she leaves her eggs to the earthand lets them be warmed on the
        ground,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'forgetting that a foot may crush themand that the wild beast may
        trample them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'She deals cruelly with her young, as if they were not hers;though
        her labor be in vain, yet she has no fear,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'because God has made her forget wisdomand given her no share in understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When she rouses herself to flee,[[COMMENT(0)]]she laughs at the horse
        and his rider.  '
      comments:
      - number: '39:18 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CDo you give the horse his might?Do you clothe his neck with
        a mane?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do you make him leap like the locust?His majestic snorting is terrifying.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He paws[[COMMENT(0)]] in the valley and exults in his strength;he
        goes out to meet the weapons.  '
      comments:
      - number: '39:21 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He laughs at fear and is not dismayed;he does not turn back from
        the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Upon him rattle the quiver,the flashing spear, and the javelin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'With fierceness and rage he swallows the ground;he cannot stand still
        at the sound of the trumpet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When the trumpet sounds, he says \u2018Aha!\u2019He smells the battle
        from afar,the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CIs it by your understanding that the hawk soarsand spreads
        his wings toward the south?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Is it at your command that the eagle mounts upand makes his nest
        on high?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'On the rock he dwells and makes his home,on the rocky crag and stronghold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From there he spies out the prey;his eyes behold it from far away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "His young ones suck up blood,and where the slain are, there is he.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  said to Job:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Job Promises Silence'
      title: Job Promises Silence
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShall a faultfinder contend with the Almighty?He who argues
        with God, let him answer it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Job answered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am of small account; what shall I answer you?  I
        lay my hand on my mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The  Challenges Job'
      title: The  Challenges Job
      number: 5
      content: "I have spoken once, and I will not answer;  twice, but I will proceed
        no further.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  answered Job out of the whirlwind
        and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CDress for action[[COMMENT(0)]] like a man;  I will question
        you, and you make it known to me.  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Will you even put me in the wrong?Will you condemn me that you may
        be in the right?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you an arm like God,and can you thunder with a voice like his?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAdorn yourself with majesty and dignity;  clothe yourself with
        glory and splendor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Pour out the overflowings of your anger,and look on everyone who
        is proud and abase him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Look on everyone who is proud and bring him lowand tread down the
        wicked where they stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Hide them all in the dust together;bind their faces in the world
        below.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '40:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then will I also acknowledge to youthat your own right hand can save
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBehold, Behemoth,[[COMMENT(0)]]which I made as I made you;he
        eats grass like an ox.  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:15 '
        content: A large animal, exact identity unknown
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Behold, his strength in his loins,and his power in the muscles of
        his belly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He makes his tail stiff like a cedar;the sinews of his thighs are
        knit together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'His bones are tubes of bronze,his limbs like bars of iron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CHe is the first of the works[[COMMENT(0)]] of God;let him who
        made him bring near his sword!  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the mountains yield food for himwhere all the wild beasts play.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Under the lotus plants he lies,in the shelter of the reeds and in
        the marsh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For his shade the lotus trees cover him;the willows of the brook
        surround him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Behold, if the river is turbulent he is not frightened;he is confident
        though Jordan rushes against his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Can one take him by his eyes,[[COMMENT(0)]]or pierce his nose with
        a snare?
      comments:
      - number: '40:24 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CCan you draw out Leviathan with a fishhookor
        press down his tongue with a cord?  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:1 '
        content: '  Ch 40:25 in Hebrew  A large sea animal, exact identity unknown  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Can you put a rope in his noseor pierce his jaw with a hook?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Will he make many pleas to you?Will he speak to you soft words?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Will he make a covenant with youto take him for your servant forever?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Will you play with him as with a bird,or will you put him on a leash
        for your girls?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Will traders bargain over him?Will they divide him up among the merchants?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Can you fill his skin with harpoonsor his head with fishing spears?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Lay your hands on him;remember the battle\u2014you will not do it
        again!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]] Behold, the hope of a man is false;he is laid low
        even at the sight of him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:9 '
        content: '  Ch 41:1 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'No one is so fierce that he dares to stir him up.Who then is he who
        can stand before me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Who has first given to me, that I should repay him?  Whatever is
        under the whole heaven is mine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI will not keep silence concerning his limbs,or his mighty
        strength, or his goodly frame.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who can strip off his outer garment?Who would come near him with
        a bridle?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who can open the doors of his face?Around his teeth is terror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'His back is made of[[COMMENT(0)]] rows of shields,shut up closely
        as with a seal.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'One is so near to anotherthat no air can come between them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They are joined one to another;they clasp each other and cannot be
        separated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'His sneezings flash forth light,and his eyes are like the eyelids
        of the dawn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Out of his mouth go flaming torches;sparks of fire leap forth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Out of his nostrils comes forth smoke,as from a boiling pot and burning
        rushes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'His breath kindles coals,and a flame comes forth from his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In his neck abides strength,and terror dances before him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The folds of his flesh stick together,firmly cast on him and immovable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'His heart is hard as a stone,hard as the lower millstone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When he raises himself up, the mighty[[COMMENT(0)]] are afraid;at
        the crashing they are beside themselves.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:25 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Though the sword reaches him, it does not avail,nor the spear, the
        dart, or the javelin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He counts iron as straw,and bronze as rotten wood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The arrow cannot make him flee;for him, sling stones are turned to
        stubble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Clubs are counted as stubble;he laughs at the rattle of javelins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'His underparts are like sharp potsherds;he spreads himself like a
        threshing sledge on the mire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He makes the deep boil like a pot;he makes the sea like a pot of
        ointment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Behind him he leaves a shining wake;one would think the deep to be
        white-haired.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  On earth there is not his like,a creature without fear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "He sees everything that is high;he is king over all the sons of pride.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Confession and Repentance"
      title: "Job\u2019s Confession and Repentance"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Job answered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI know that you can do all things,and that no purpose of yours
        can be thwarted.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u2018Who is this that hides counsel without knowledge?\u2019Therefore
        I have uttered what I did not understand,things too wonderful for me, which
        I did not know.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Hear, and I will speak;  I will question you, and you make
        it known to me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I had heard of you by the hearing of the ear,but now my eye sees
        you;  '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: The  Rebukes Job\u2019s Friends"
      title: "The  Rebukes Job\u2019s Friends"
      number: 6
      content: "therefore I despise myself,and repent[[COMMENT(0)]] in dust and ashes.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '42:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "After the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had spoken these words to Job,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Eliphaz the Temanite: \u201CMy anger
        burns against you and against your two friends, for you have not spoken of
        me what is right, as my servant Job has. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now therefore take seven bulls and seven rams and go to my servant
        Job and offer up a burnt offering for yourselves. And my servant Job shall
        pray for you, for I will accept his prayer not to deal with you according
        to your folly. For you have not spoken of me what is right, as my servant
        Job has.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: The  Restores Job\u2019s Fortunes"
      title: "The  Restores Job\u2019s Fortunes"
      number: 9
      content: "So Eliphaz the Temanite and Bildad the Shuhite and Zophar the Naamathite
        went and did what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had told them, and the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> accepted Job\u2019s prayer.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  restored the fortunes of Job,
        when he had prayed for his friends. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave
        Job twice as much as he had before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then came to him all his brothers and sisters and all who had known
        him before, and ate bread with him in his house. And they showed him sympathy
        and comforted him for all the evil[[COMMENT(0)]] that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had brought upon him. And each of them gave him a piece of money and a ring
        of gold.  '
      comments:
      - number: '42:11 '
        content: Or Hebrew ; a unit of money of unknown value
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> blessed the latter days of Job
        more than his beginning. And he had 14,000 sheep, 6,000 camels, 1,000 yoke
        of oxen, and 1,000 female donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He had also seven sons and three daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he called the name of the first daughter Jemimah, and the name
        of the second Keziah, and the name of the third Keren-happuch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And in all the land there were no women so beautiful as Job\u2019s
        daughters. And their father gave them an inheritance among their brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And after this Job lived 140 years, and saw his sons, and his sons\u2019
        sons, four generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And Job died, an old man, and full of days.
      comments: []
